   Description
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Slalom simulation game.


   System requirements
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Any amiga.


   Installation
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Copy Slalom in a directory of your choice.


   Usage
   ¯¯¯¯¯
   Open a CLI/Shell window, enter the Slalom directory, type in 'Slalom' and
   press the Enter key.
   Choose a track (1÷8) and compete with all 20 skiers in two runs.
   Push fire to start every competitor and move the joystick right and left
   to guide it along the run. Move the joystick up and down to
   decrease/increase the speed. You must get over the blue flags on the
   right and the red flags on the left. The more precise your trajectories
   are the less the final time is.
   Press F1 to pass to the following skyer.
   Press F6 at any time to restart the game.
   Press F10 during the title to quit the game.


